commit_list.message:
Fix packaging trying to modify unrelated files

`package()` method in `setup.py` tries to compile and chmod all files
under the directory given by `--prefix PREFIX`.

If PREFIX is a directory containing other distributions (like
`/usr/local` or `$HOME/.local`), then it would try to compile - using
possibly the wrong python version - and chmod all files within PREFIX.

Fix #42 for rake tasks

The original issue #42 doesn't specifically states whether the problem
happens by using the rake task or CLI, but while the CLI is fixed by
later changes, the rake task is still broken. It tries to compare model
names that comes in an array of symbols via
`options.only`/`options.exclude` against String model names.

This keeps both CLIs (rake and binary) consistent in handling
comma-separated values. The binary CLI splits into an array of strings,
which the rake task should too.

commit_list.message:
Refactor and fix protobuf generation:

* Extracted protobuf package definitions to `config.json` which will be
  unmarshaled by `gen.go` into the newly created `genConfig` type.
* gen.go no longer executes `protoc` directly. Instead, it generates
  a package file stub which contains `go generate` directives which will
  execute `protoc`. Those stub files are called `generate.go` and are
  generated from the template in `generate.go.template`.
* gen.go itself contains a `go generate` directive that will call
  `generate.sh` which will run the whole generation process. In this
  way, simply running `go generate` at the top of the repository path
  will run the whole generation. To make this work, `gen.go` needs to be
  part of the build process, so the directive to ignore the file when
  building was removed.
* Previous generated protobufs were incorrect because testing was done
  using `go build ./protobuf`, which doesn't cover protobuf's
  subpackages. It was fixed by changing package definitions accordingly
  and testing with `go build ./protobuf/...`.
* Removed generation of the vendored `google/protobuf` package.
  `proto-gen-go` no longer requires it.
